&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Corporate Controller, the Accounting Manager will own the financial close process for Feastables and other CPG areas, ensure regulatory and banking compliance, and maintain the integrity of financial reporting. You will serve as a key partner during external audits, collaborate with cross-functional leaders, support system implementations, and drive process improvements to accelerate the close cycle. This role is ideal for a hands-on operator with a strong technical foundation and a builder mentality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute all core accounting operations, including Billing, Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, General Ledger, Cost Accounting, Inventory Accounting, and Revenue Recognition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify financial risks and opportunities in partnership with key internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and maintain scalable financial systems, controls, and processes to support accurate forecasting and budgeting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with GAAP, tax requirements, and industry regulations, delivering accurate and timely financial reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage inventory accounting and balance sheet integrity, including annual and ongoing reconciliations within NetSuite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own monthly close, compliance reporting, and variance analysis to support continuous performance improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Supply Chain to ensure accurate, timely, and actionable financial reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee controllership responsibilities, including inventory management and internal controls execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
