&lt;p&gt;Beast Industries is a multifaceted media and entertainment company founded by Jimmy Donaldson, popularly known as MrBeast, the most watched person in the world. Renowned for revolutionizing digital content creation, Beast Industries encompasses a diverse portfolio of ventures that extend far beyond its origins on YouTube. With a mission to entertain, inspire, and create significant social impact, Beast Industries operates across various domains including digital media, philanthropy, consumer products, and innovative business initiatives. At Beast Industries, we believe in the transformative power of digital media and its potential to entertain, educate, and effect positive change. Our commitment to innovation, creativity, and philanthropy drives us to explore new frontiers, create unforgettable experiences, and build a legacy that inspires future generations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beast Industries is building products and services for consumers and creators around community participation, memberships, interactive experiences, creator tools, and commercial partnerships. As the company expands globally, the legal team plays a critical role in enabling growth while managing regulatory, consumer, privacy, and commercial risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate General Counsel, Product &amp;amp; Commercial serves as a primary legal partner to the teams responsible for the Beast Membership program and Global Creator Platform. This role provides legal guidance across product development, partnerships, subscriptions, promotions, creator ecosystems, live experiences, and global expansion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns legal support for consumer-facing products, creator platform initiatives, and commercial partnerships. The position partners closely with Product, Engineering, Content, Marketing, Partnerships, and Finance to help launch and scale new offerings while maintaining appropriate legal and regulatory safeguards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is responsible for advising on product features, subscription models, promotions, privacy and online safety requirements, commercial agreements, creator ecosystem expansion, and global growth initiatives. It also serves as a key advisor on high-sensitivity areas including privacy compliance, winner verification processes, and global regulatory requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as lead legal in-house counsel for the Beast Membership program, the Creator Global Platform and strategic partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on new applications, products, features, and business models to identify and mitigate legal risks across multiple jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Counsel stakeholders on consumer protection, privacy, data protection, competition, intellectual property, and emerging regulatory frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure and advise on subscription offerings, including free trials, referral programs, membership benefits, and related consumer disclosures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide legal support for challenges, prize structures, and production-related legal considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and oversee sweepstakes, contest, and promotion frameworks, including official rules, eligibility requirements, and prize fulfillment considerations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead legal workstreams related to winner verification, age verification, and know-your-customer requirements for high-value prizes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on data privacy including COPPA-related requirements and compliant product experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support rewards and commerce ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on content licensing, creator programming, and cont

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beast Industries is a multifaceted media and entertainment company founded by Jimmy Donaldson, popularly known as MrBeast, the most watched person in the world. Renowned for revolutionizing digital content creation, Beast Industries encompasses a diverse portfolio of ventures that extend far beyond its origins on YouTube. With a mission to entertain, inspire, and create significant social impact, Beast Industries operates across various domains including digital media, philanthropy, consumer products, and innovative business initiatives. At Beast Industries, we believe in the transformative power of digital media and its potential to entertain, educate, and effect positive change. Our commitment to innovation, creativity, and philanthropy drives us to explore new frontiers, create unforgettable experiences, and build a legacy that inspires future generations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team: Finance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: New York, NY or Surrounding Areas&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Strategic Finance team, you will help scale the financial reporting, analytics, and planning capabilities and empower decision makers across our different businesses and functions. You will play a key role in all aspects of financial reporting and make significant contributions to high-profile strategic and operational initiatives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Associate, Strategic Finance at MrBeast, you’ll help build and scale the planning infrastructure that guides our strategic and operational decisions. Sitting at the intersection of growth, strategy, and performance, this role is critical to driving financial visibility and rigor across the organization. This is a highly cross-functional role, partnering closely with leaders across Finance, Operations, and Executive teams to translate company priorities into structured financial plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re excited by solving ambiguity, building structure from scratch, and influencing high-impact decisions, this is an opportunity to help shape the financial backbone of one of the most exciting brands in the space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and evolve our strategic finance rhythm, including annual planning, forecasting, monthly reviews, and long-range models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with business leaders and finance stakeholders to develop budgets and track performance across revenue and operating costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and improve forecasting accuracy and transparency across teams through strong models and operational processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive development of financial frameworks that align investment decisions with strategic priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create executive-ready reports and insights that help tell the story of our business, including board and investor materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale dashboards, planning tools, and systems to support real-time decision making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and solve cross-functional planning challenges, helping bridge strategic goals with financial execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ad hoc analysis to evaluate new initiatives, business cases, or shifts in operating strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in strategic planning roles, ideally in high-growth or consumer-facing industries. Early Experience in investment banking and/or consulting is highly desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and managing financial planning processes in dynamic, fast-paced environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong modeling and analytica

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beast Industries is a multifaceted media and entertainment company founded by Jimmy Donaldson, popularly known as MrBeast, the most watched person in the world. Renowned for revolutionizing digital content creation, Beast Industries encompasses a diverse portfolio of ventures that extend far beyond its origins on YouTube. With a mission to entertain, inspire, and create significant social impact, Beast Industries operates across various domains including digital media, philanthropy, consumer products, and innovative business initiatives. At Beast Industries, we believe in the transformative power of digital media and its potential to entertain, educate, and effect positive change. Our commitment to innovation, creativity, and philanthropy drives us to explore new frontiers, create unforgettable experiences, and build a legacy that inspires future generations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Brand Activation Manager&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong&gt;MrBeast&lt;/strong&gt;, you are the operational engine and the “hot standby” for our Brand Activation Leads. We produce high-stakes, unscripted content where plans change by the minute. Your job is to stabilize that chaos.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You manage the logistical and executional reality of complex campaigns end to end, spanning legal compliance, physical logistics, data integrity, and on-set client management. While creative plans may evolve in real time, you ensure that every contractual “must-have” is delivered.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role is preferably based in the Greenville, NC area and operates 100% in-office, five days per week, except during weeks when production requires weekend work. You will work closely with Production, Legal, Sales, and external clients under tight timelines and shifting conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campaign Lifecycle &amp;amp; KPI Intelligence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track every campaign element from pre-production through final wrap using Monday.com and own the status of complex, high-value deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Campaign Wrap Report process for internal archives and external client presentations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and validate performance data from internal and external sources (Viewstats, Google Analytics) to update the central KPI database&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary post-sale liaison to Legal, including sweepstakes and contest rules, scope changes, amended terms, and written client approvals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce data integrity across Monday.com and Boostr, ensuring all inputs are clean, standardized, and properly tagged&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Production Logistics &amp;amp; Asset Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the physical logistics of productions, including product deliveries to set, contest prizing fulfillment, and inventory tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee compliance requirements from third parties such as streamers, including legal clearances, music cue sheets, and talent releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with editors post-production to ensure all client deliverables are met and timelines are maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools (Gemini Pro, Nano, Veo, Canvas) to streamline administrative workflows and asset management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On-Set Execution &amp;amp; Client Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the immediate backup and right hand to the Brand Activation Lead during shoots, troubleshooting issues so Leads can remain focused on strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage on-set client hospitality and experience with professionalism under pressure

